[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`@relay-assistant/surfaces` manages the connections between the assistant [39m      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mruntime and user-facing interaction mediums. A surface is any channel through [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mwhich a user sends messages to or receives messages from the assistant (web [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mchat, Slack, desktop, API, etc.).[39m                                               [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Owns:**[39m                                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `SurfaceConnection` — registered connection to one surface; carries inbound [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mand outbound contracts[39m                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `SurfaceRegistry` — tracks all registered surface connections; routes [39m        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231moutbound events to the correct adapter[39m                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Inbound normalization — converts surface-specific raw payloads into [39m          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`InboundMessage` before handing to core[39m                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `RelayInboundAdapter` and `RelayOutboundAdapter` implementation — [39m            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`SurfaceRegistry` implements both core adapter interfaces, acting as the bridge[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m between the relay foundation and core[39m                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Outbound dispatch — converts `OutboundEvent` from core into surface-specific [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mformat via format hooks[39m                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Fanout �� when a session has multiple attached surfaces, deliver an outbound [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mevent to all of them (with configurable policy)[39m                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Format hooks — product-supplied functions that transform text + metadata into[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m surface-specific structures (Slack block kit, markdown, plain text, etc.)[39m      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Surface capability advertising — surfaces may declare what formatting [39m        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +1974 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
